      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A strong, sophisticated argument centers on national sovereignty and the rule of law; uncontrolled borders undermine the very foundation of a functional nation-state. Furthermore, enhanced security is a critical component of national security, directly addressing threats from transnational criminal organizations and individuals intent on illegal entry. Focusing on the economic impact of rigorous enforcement allows students to argue that orderly immigration stabilizes labor markets and protects domestic industries.",
